    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I compiled my pyx with cython successfully and imported it as a library. All the functions work, except for the udfs. I got error messages like this:\r\nCan't pickle <cyfunction my_class_name.my_method_name.<locals>.my_udf_name at 0x7f74580b4c80>\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if it's because cython can't work with pyspark udf, or it's just my code. But my code works fine when not compiled.",
    "closed_at": "2018-09-21T17:01:37Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "You need to use a global function, not a local one. Nested functions work in Python code because Python can pickle them including their byte code. For compiled functions, there is no byte code that could be pickled, so the state can be pickled and transferred, but the function itself must be accessible on the other side. Local functions are not accessible from anywhere outside of the function that defines it.",
